This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 18 through September 24, 2011, as National Hispanic-Serving Institutions Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of providing equal opportunities in education for all young Americans, including Hispanics. It recognizes the role of Hispanic-Serving Institutions (HSIs) in helping Hispanic students access higher education and develop skills necessary for success in the 21st century. The proclamation also highlights the efforts to improve educational outcomes for Hispanic students, expand access to pre-kindergarten programs, reduce high school dropout rates, and recruit more Hispanic teachers and school leaders. It calls on public officials, educators, and the people of the United States to observe the week with programs and activities that acknowledge the contributions of HSIs and their graduates to the country.